<font color="#FF0000">REPLY TO PAUL</font><br>
<tt>Sat Apr  5 15:31:27 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
To Paul:<br><br>
Your words are well spoken. They are a clear elucidation of your opinion. I do not share in your opinion.<br><br>
I find I am not like an automata that can change circuits on a wish, a prayer, or a command. It is a laudible life objective to put things &quot;behind&quot; and move forward , but to ascribe that quality with certainty to others is mistaken.<br><br>
I once said on this site:<br><br>
&quot;My Vietnam past follows me around at times like a lost puppy and at times like a case of the flu.&quot;<br><br>
This is still my reality, my truth, and will be so for a long time to come. To acknowledge otherwise would be denial of the highest order, and would result in a classic train wreck in my mind. I have come to regard myself in terms better than those which would allow that to occurr.<br><br>
You said:<br><br>
&quot;Like the war and the experience, it is time to put the site behind us.&quot;<br><br>
It is not in my &quot;time&quot; to do so.<br><br>
    
<p><code>-- Art16@ix.netcom.com  (Arthur Varanelli) </code><p>


